A secret network of ordinary people known as the Underground Railroad guide the family on their journey north to Canada. They are relentlessly pursued by the notorious slave-hunter Plimpton. Hunted like a dog and haunted by the unthinkable suffering he and his forbears have endured, Samuel is forced to decide between revenge or freedom. 100 years earlier in 1748, John Newton the Captain of a slave ship sails from Africa with a cargo of slaves, bound for America. On board is Samuel's great-grandfather, whose survival is tied to the fate of Captain Newton. The voyage changes Newton's life forever and he creates a legacy that will inspire Samuel and the lives of millions for generations to come.

description: Veera, a young bride-to-be, is abducted by a local gangster, Mahabir, and his men a day prior to her wedding. Far from being terrified of her abductor, Veera discovers a new meaning to her life.

title: Simmba
description: Simmba, a corrupt police officer, works for Durva, an influential smuggler. However, his life takes an unusual turn when he decides to avenge a woman who was assaulted by Durva's brothers.

title: Raazi
description: Sehmat Khan, an undercover RAW agent, is married into a Pakistani family by her father so that she can get some valuable piece of information about the enemy.\n

title: Rustom
description: Rustom, a naval officer, shares a happy relationship with his wife Cynthia. Soon, he discovers her affair with Vikram, a close friend, and is accused of murdering him.

title: Madras Cafe
description: Vikram, an Indian intelligence agent who visits Sri Lanka on a secret mission, finds himself embroiled in a civil war and a conspiracy to kill the former prime minister of India.

title: Wazir
description: When his daughter is killed by the terrorist he is chasing, Daanish, a cop, swears to seek revenge. He finds a confidante in Pandit, an unassuming grand master, also mourning the loss of his daughter.
genre: Crime, Thriller, Mystery, Drama, Conspiracy Thriller

title: Udaan
description: After being expelled from school, Rohan returns home to a strict father as well as a half-brother he was unaware of. He is forced to work at his father's factory even though he wants to write.

title: Parmanu: The Story of Pokhran
description: IAS officer Ashwat is tasked to lead an operation to develop and test nuclear weapons but must ensure that American intelligence agencies do not learn about it.
writer: Saiwyn Quadras, Abhishek Sharma, Sanyuktha Chawla Shaikh

title: Baazaar
description: An amateur stock trader, Rizwan, goes to Mumbai and works for the successful Gujarati trader, Shakun Kothari. Everything seems to be going smoothly until Rizwan faces betrayal from his idol.

title: Anek
description: Joshua, a covert officer sent to handle peace talks in a disturbed Northeast India, runs into Aido, an aspiring boxer who is racially abused but still dreams of winning the gold medal for her country.

title: Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety
description: Childhood friends Sonu and Titu's friendship is tested when an innocent Titu decides to marry Sweety, who is not just behind his money but is hell-bent on breaking their friendship too.

title: Gold
description: Tapan Das is responsible for managing the Indian hockey team after independence. He strives to overcome many obstacles in order to earn a gold medal in the Olympics for his country.
writer: Reema Kagti, Rajesh Devraj, Javed Akhtar

title: Badlapur
description: Raghu loses his wife and son when two bank robbers steal their car in a bid to run. Devastated by the incident, Raghu decides to take revenge on the culprits, Liak and Harman, for killing his family.

title: Masaan
description: In Varanasi, Devi struggles to shake off the social stigma of pre-marital sexual relations. Meanwhile, lovers Deepak and Shalu attempt to transcend the restrictions of their casteist society.

title: Gangubai Kathiawadi
description: Gangubai Kathiawadi is a biographical crime drama that chronicles the life of Gangubai Kothewali, a young woman from Kathiawad who is deceived and sold into prostitution in Mumbai's Kamathipura district. Rising above her circumstances, she becomes a formidable madam of the brothel and a powerful figure advocating for the rights of sex workers.

title: Kai Po Che!
description: Three friends start an academy to train aspiring cricketers. But before they realise their goals, they experience an earthquake, an unstable political situation and communal riots.
writer: Pubali Chaudhari, Supratik Sen, Abhishek Kapoor, Chetan Bhagat

title: War
description: Kabir, a secret agent, goes rogue after a mission to catch a terrorist goes awry. However, his boss sends Khalid, another agent and his student, to track him down.
writer: Siddharth Anand, Aditya Chopra, Shridhar Raghavan, Abbas Tyrewala

title: Rockstar
description: College student Janardhan is a simpleton who desperately seeks inspiration for the musician inside him. Although heartbreak helps him reach his goal, it also leads him to self-destruction.

title: Tamasha
description: Ved and Tara fall in love while on a holiday in Corsica and decide to keep their real identities undisclosed. Tara returns to Delhi and meets a new Ved, who is trying to discover his true self.

title: Aligarh
description: Dr Shrinivas Ramchandra Siras, a professor on whom a sting operation was carried out to determine his sexual orientation, forms a special bond with the journalist who covers his story.

title: Sui Dhaaga
description: Mauji, along with his wife, Mamta, decides to start his own garment business. To make a name for himself, he enlists the help of various artisans and participates in a renowned fashion competition.

title: Jersey
description: A talented but failed cricketer decides to return to cricket in his late thirties driven by the desire to represent the Indian team and fulfil his son's wish for a jersey as a gift.

title: October
description: Dan and Shiuli are brought closer in an unexpected turn of events. Eventually, they develop feelings for each other and establish a bond unlike any other which leads to an internal awakening.

title: Dhamaal
description: Four lazy friends named Roy, Manav, Aditya and Boman venture out on a race to find a hidden treasure in Goa. However, Inspector Kabir soon learns about their plan and sets out on their trail.
writer: Balvinder Singh Suri, Paritosh Painter, Bunty Rathore

title: Golmaal
description: Friends Gopal, Lucky, Madhav and Laxman often dupe gullible people out of their money. Hilarity ensues when they target a middle-aged couple and simultaneously try wooing their beautiful neighbour.

title: Andaz Apna Apna
description: Amar and Prem, who belong to middle-class families, compete to win over Raveena, a millionaire's daughter. Along the way, they run into a local gangster, Teja, who turns their lives upside down.

title: Hera Pheri
description: Two tenants and a landlord, in desperate need of money, chance upon a ransom call via a cross connection. They hatch a plan to claim the ransom for themselves.\n

title: Garam Masala
description: Shyam and Makarand, two photographer friends, like to flirt with women constantly. After a trip abroad, Shyam decides to disrupt Makarand's life when he sees him enjoying the company of three ladies.

title: Hungama
description: A millionaire businessman living in a village decides to move to the city with his wife. They soon get into a case of mistaken identity that results in comical situations.

title: Ishq
description: Businessmen Ranjit and Harbanslal want their children Ajay and Madhu to marry each other. However, Madhu falls in love with Raja, a mechanic, while Ajay falls in love with Kajal, a poor woman.
writer: Tanveer Khan, Rajeev Kaul, Praful Parekh, Naushir Khatau

title: Bhool Bhulaiyaa
description: An NRI and his wife decide to stay in his ancestral home, paying no heed to the warnings about ghosts. Soon, inexplicable occurrences cause him to call a psychiatrist to help solve the mystery.

title: Phir Hera Pheri
description: A twist of fate changes the lives of Raju, Shyam and Baburao when they get cheated by a fraudster. They must now find another way to repay the loan taken from a dreaded gangster.

title: Dhol
description: Four lazy friends want to make easy money and aim to marry a rich girl. Their plan backfires after they meet Ritu and get embroiled with a dangerous criminal.

title: Heyy Babyy
description: Three compulsive womanisers find a baby left at their doorstep. However, chaos ensues as they try to contact their former girlfriends to determine who is the father amongst them.
writer: Sajid Khan, Milap Zaveri, Renuka Kunzru

title: Ajab Prem Ki Ghazab Kahani
description: Prem falls in love with Jenny, a woman who is already in love with a man named Rahul. Despite this, he agrees to help her marry him and even gets into several comical situations as a result.
writer: Rajkumar Santoshi, K. Rajeshwar, R.D. Tailang, K Rajeshwar

title: Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge
description: Raj and Simran meet during a trip across Europe and the two fall in love. However, when Raj learns that Simran is already promised to another, he follows her to India to win her and her father over.

title: Kuch Kuch Hota Hai
description: A tomboyish Anjali loves Rahul, her best college pal, but is anguished when he decides to wed Tina, a fellow collegian. Eight years later, widower Rahul's daughter is told to reunite him with Anjali.

title: Om Shanti Om
description: Om, a junior film artist, is smitten by Shantipriya, a renowned actress, but is killed while trying to save her from a fire accident. Thirty years later, he is reborn and sets out to avenge her death.
genre: Action, Comedy, Drama, Fantasy, Romance, Thriller
writer: Farah Khan, Mayur Puri, Mushtaq Sheikh

title: Mohabbatein
description: Narayan is a strict principal of Gurukul who does not believe in love and forbids his students from following their hearts. However, things take a turn when a music teacher challenges his authority.

title: Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham...
description: The adopted but much loved elder son of a rich couple is banished by his father when he chooses to wed a middle-class woman. Their younger son sets out to find him, hoping to reunite his family.

title: Raees
description: Threat looms over bootlegger Raees Alam and his business after ACP Majmudar decides to get the better of him. In order to survive and keep his trade thriving, Raees must overcome Majumdar.

title: Chennai Express
description: Rahul, a young man, sets out to immerse his late grandfather's ashes at Rameshwaram. However, when he helps Meena, a runaway bride, board a train, he has to face the ire of her criminal family.

title: Baby John
description: Baby John is a 2024 Indian Hindi-language action drama film directed by Kalees. It serves as a remake of Atlee's 2016 Tamil film Theri. The film stars Varun Dhawan, alongside Keerthy Suresh, Wamiqa Gabbi, Zara Zyanna and Jackie Shroff.

title: Tere Naam
description: Radhe, a rowdy boy, falls in love with Nirjara, a first year college student. After initial hatred, when Nirjara reciprocates his love, a brutal attack renders him mentally unstable.

title: Dabangg
description: Chulbul Pandey is a cop who has his own way of dealing with corruption. His detractor Cheddi Singh manages to create a rift between Chulbul and his step-brother and uses it to his advantage.

title: Bodyguard
description: Lovely, an expert bodyguard, comes to the rescue of Divya, a wealthy businessman's daughter whose security is at risk. Eventually, they become close and develop genuine feelings for each other.

title: Pink
description: After being molested, Minal, along with her friends, tries to file an FIR against a politician's nephew. When the subsequent case gets rigged, Deepak, a retired lawyer, helps them to fight the case.
writer: Aniruddha Roy Chowdhury, Shoojit Sircar, Ritesh Shah

title: Karthik Calling Karthik
description: Karthik, an introvert, is always ridiculed by his boss and has faced many setbacks throughout his life. However, one day, he receives a phone call from a stranger who promises to transform his life.

title: Bell Bottom
description: When a flight is hijacked by terrorists, Anshul, an undercover agent, sets out to rescue the passengers held hostage. However, he must overcome several challenges to be successful in his quest.

title: Badla
description: Naina, a successful entrepreneur and married woman, gets caught in a web of accusations when her lover is found dead. She then hires a reputable lawyer to work with her on the case and find answers.

title: Shivaay
description: To unite his daughter, Gaura, with her Bulgarian mother, Olga, Shivaay travels overseas. On the way, a child trafficker kidnaps Gaura, causing Shivaay to chase him.

title: D-Day
description: Intelligence officer Wali Khan and a team of highly-trained officers are set to nab Goldman, one of India's most wanted terrorists. However, their mission is threatened by a minor miscalculation.
writer: Nikkhil Advani, Ritesh Shah, Suresh Nair

title: Ugly
description: Rahul, a struggling actor, searches for his daughter, Kali, after she goes missing. Soon, he and Bose, her stepfather who is also a policeman, begin to accuse each other of kidnapping her.

title: Neerja
description: Neerja, a flight attendant, boards Pan Am flight 73 in 1986. When the flight is hijacked by terrorists, Neerja risks her life to stall the terrorists from attacking the passengers on board.

title: Rocky Handsome
description: Kabir, a young man who runs a pawn shop in Goa, befriends his little neighbour Naomi, a bright eight-year-old girl. After she gets abducted, he goes on a vengeful spree to get her back.\n

title: Talaash: The Answer Lies Within
description: Inspector Shekhawat and his wife are stunned when their son dies. While his wife openly struggles to deal with her loss, he distracts himself by solving the mysterious death of an actor.
writer: Farhan Akhtar, Anurag Kashyap, Zoya Akhtar

title: Force
description: ACP Yashvardhan of the Narcotics Control Bureau and his team successfully kill a drug dealer, Vasu. But Vasu's vengeful brother, Vishnu, a dreaded gangster, vows to destroy the ACP's life.

title: Don 2
description: After dominating the Asian underworld, Don sets his eyes on the European criminal market. Caught between the Berlin mafia and law enforcement, Don tries to escape treachery and betrayal.

title: Sherni
description: A forest officer is tasked with capturing and containing a man-eating tigress in a remote village. However, she faces hostility from various sides as she tries to do her job.\n

title: Raajneeti
description: Samar, the son of a political family, has chosen to go to the USA to live with his girlfriend. However, the death of his father makes him put his plans on hold and enter the dirty world of politics.
writer: Prakash Jha, Anjum Rajabali, Sameer Anjaan

title: Udta Punjab
description: A rock star, a migrant labourer, a doctor and a policeman find themselves struggling to cope with the ensuing chaos surrounding a drug crisis in Punjab, India.

title: Once Upon a Time in Mumbaai
description: Two gangsters, Sultan Mirza, the infamous mobster of Mumbai, and Shoaib Khan, who aims to create an image in the underworld, try their best to rule the city on their own terms.

title: Rann
description: Vijay Malik runs his struggling television channel with integrity despite stiff competition. However, his son Jai concocts a plan to take over the business via a fake news story.

title: Ishqiya
description: Khalujan and Babban, two rogues, fall in love with Krishna, their friend's widow. However, Krishna manipulates them into carrying out her bidding for her selfish gain.
writer: Vishal Bhardwaj, Sabrina Dhawan, Abhishek Chaubey

title: The Creator
description: As a future war between the human race and artificial intelligence rages on, ex-special forces agent Joshua is recruited to hunt down and kill the Creator, the elusive architect of advanced AI. The Creator has developed a mysterious weapon that has the power to end the war and all of mankind.

title: Red One
description: When a villain kidnaps Santa Claus from the North Pole, an E.L.F. (Extremely Large and Formidable) operative joins forces with the world's most accomplished tracker to find him and save Christmas.

title: Hit Man
description: Professional killer Gary Johnson breaks protocol to help a desperate woman trying to flee an abusive husband and finds himself falling for her.

title: The Substance
description: Elisabeth Sparkle, renowned for an aerobics show, faces a devastating blow on her 50th birthday as her boss fires her. Amid her distress, a laboratory offers her a substance which promises to transform her into an enhanced version of herself.

title: The First Omen
description: A woman starts to question her own faith when she uncovers a terrifying conspiracy to bring about the birth of evil incarnate in Rome.
writer: Arkasha Stevenson, Keith Thomas, Tim Smith

title: Reptile
description: Following the brutal murder of a young real estate agent, a hardened detective attempts to uncover the truth in a case where nothing is as it seems, and, by doing so, dismantles the illusions in his own life.
writer: Benicio del Toro, Grant Singer, Benjamin Brewer

title: Infinity Pool
description: Guided by a seductive and mysterious woman, a couple on vacation venture outside the resort grounds and find themselves in a culture filled with violence, hedonism and untold horror. A tragic accident soon leaves them facing a zero tolerance policy for crime.

title: MaXXXine
description: In 1980s Hollywood, adult film star and aspiring actress Maxine Minx finally gets her big break. However, as a mysterious killer stalks the starlets of Los Angeles, a trail of blood threatens to reveal her sinister past.

title: Killers of the Flower Moon
description: Real love crosses paths with unspeakable betrayal as Mollie Burkhart, a member of the Osage Nation, tries to save her community from a spree of murders fueled by oil and greed.
writer: Eric Roth, Martin Scorsese, David Grann

title: The Killer
description: In this reimagining of John Woo's 1989 classic, an assassin named Zee unintentionally harms a young singer during a mission. Stricken by guilt, she seeks to make amends, but finds herself pursued by her former associates and a determined detective.
writer: Brian Helgeland, Josh Campbell, Matt Stuecken

title: The Big Short
description: "The Big Short" follows three separate but parallel stories of individuals who predicted and profited from the U.S. mortgage housing crisis of 2005. Through their own research, they discovered that the U.S. mortgage-backed securities market was a bubble about to burst, and they invested accordingly.

title: The Revenant
description: In the 1820s, frontiersman Hugh Glass embarks on a fur trading expedition in the uncharted American wilderness. After being brutally mauled by a bear, he is left for dead by members of his own hunting team. Against all odds, Glass fights for survival, driven by sheer will and a desire for vengeance against those who abandoned him.
writer: Mark L. Smith, Alejandro G. Iñárritu

title: The Town
description: Four thieves loot a bank and take the bank manager as hostage. They let her go and one of them keeps a tab on her movements to stop her from going to the police. Eventually, he falls in love with her.
writer: Ben Affleck, Peter Craig, Aaron Stockard

title: Tron: Legacy
description: Sam Flynn, a 27-year-old tech-savvy rebel, is haunted by the mysterious disappearance of his father, Kevin Flynn, a former leading video-game developer. When Sam investigates a strange signal from his father's old arcade, he is pulled into the digital world of the Grid. In this high-tech universe, Sam encounters a myriad of programs, including the warrior Quorra and the tyrannical Clu, a program created by his father. Together, Sam and Quorra embark on a life-and-death journey to find Kevin and escape the Grid.

title: 127 Hours
description: "127 Hours" is the true story of mountain climber Aron Ralston's remarkable adventure to save himself after a fallen boulder crashes on his arm and traps him in an isolated canyon in Utah. Over the next five days, Ralston examines his life and survives the elements to finally discover he has the courage and the wherewithal to extricate himself by any means necessary, scale a 65-foot wall, and hike over eight miles before he can be rescued.

title: Ocean's 8
description: Debbie Ocean, the sister of Danny Ocean, gathers an all-female crew to attempt an impossible heist at New York City's annual Met Gala.

title: Blade Runner 2049
description: Thirty years after the events of the first film, Officer K (Ryan Gosling), a new blade runner for the Los Angeles Police Department, uncovers a long-buried secret that has the potential to plunge what's left of society into chaos. His discovery leads him to Rick Deckard (Harrison Ford), a former blade runner who has been missing for three decades.

title: Justice League
description: In "Justice League," Batman and Wonder Woman work quickly to recruit a team to stand against a newly awakened enemy. Together, they assemble a team of metahumans, including Aquaman, Cyborg, and The Flash, to face the threat posed by Steppenwolf and his Parademons.

title: Birdman
description: "Birdman" follows Riggan Thomson (Michael Keaton), a washed-up actor famous for portraying an iconic superhero, as he struggles to mount a Broadway play. In the days leading up to opening night, he battles his ego and attempts to recover his family, his career, and himself.
writer: Alejandro González Iñárritu, Nicolás Giacobone, Alexander Dinelaris Jr., Armando Bo

title: Captain America: The Winter Soldier
description: After the events of "The Avengers," Steve Rogers (Chris Evans) is adjusting to modern life in Washington, D.C. When a S.H.I.E.L.D. colleague is attacked, he teams up with Black Widow (Scarlett Johansson) and new ally Falcon (Anthony Mackie) to uncover a conspiracy that threatens global security.

title: Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them
description: Set in 1926, the film follows magizoologist Newt Scamander (Eddie Redmayne) as he arrives in New York City with a suitcase full of magical creatures. When some of these creatures escape, Newt teams up with No-Maj Jacob Kowalski (Dan Fogler), witch Tina Goldstein (Katherine Waterston), and her sister Queenie (Alison Sudol) to recapture them, all while uncovering dark forces threatening the wizarding world.

title: Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom
description: Three years after the destruction of Jurassic World, Owen Grady (Chris Pratt) and Claire Dearing (Bryce Dallas Howard) return to Isla Nublar to rescue the remaining dinosaurs from an impending volcanic eruption. Their mission becomes complicated as they uncover a sinister plot that threatens the future of both humans and dinosaurs.

title: La La Land
description: "La La Land" is a musical romantic comedy-drama that follows the love story between a jazz pianist, Sebastian (Ryan Gosling), and an aspiring actress, Mia (Emma Stone), as they pursue their dreams in Los Angeles. The film explores themes of ambition, love, and the sacrifices made in the pursuit of artistic passion.

title: Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald
description: In 1927, dark wizard Gellert Grindelwald escapes custody and begins gathering followers to establish a pure-blood wizarding regime. Albus Dumbledore enlists former student Newt Scamander to thwart Grindelwald's plans, leading to a series of events that test loyalties and reveal hidden truths.

title: Red
description: Frank Moses (Bruce Willis), a retired CIA agent, is forced back into action when a high-tech assassin targets him. To survive, he reassembles his old team, including Joe (Morgan Freeman), Marvin (John Malkovich), and Victoria (Helen Mirren), leading to a series of explosive adventures.

title: Pacific Rim
description: When colossal sea creatures known as Kaiju emerge from a breach in the Pacific Ocean, humanity's last line of defense is a series of massive robots called Jaegers, piloted by two individuals whose minds are linked. Former pilot Raleigh Becket (Charlie Hunnam) is recruited to join forces with rookie Mako Mori (Rinko Kikuchi) to combat the Kaiju threat.

title: The Mummy
description: An ancient princess (Sofia Boutella) awakens from her crypt beneath the desert, bringing with her malevolence grown over millennia and terrors that defy human comprehension.
writer: David Koepp, Christopher McQuarrie, Dylan Kussman

title: The Lion King
description: Simba, a young lion prince, flees his kingdom after the murder of his father, Mufasa. He learns the true meaning of responsibility and bravery as he returns to reclaim his rightful throne.

title: Dark Phoenix
description: Jean Grey (Sophie Turner) begins to develop incredible powers that corrupt and turn her into the Dark Phoenix, causing the X-Men to have to decide if her life is worth more than all of humanity.

title: Mission: Impossible - Fallout
description: Ethan Hunt (Tom Cruise) and his IMF team, along with some familiar allies, race against time after a mission gone wrong.

title: Spider-Man: Far From Home
description: Peter Parker (Tom Holland) embarks on a school trip to Europe, where he faces new challenges as Spider-Man. He is recruited by Nick Fury (Samuel L. Jackson) to help uncover the mystery of elemental creature attacks across the continent, leading to an alliance with the enigmatic Mysterio (Jake Gyllenhaal).

title: Looper
description: In the year 2044, time travel has not yet been invented. But in 30 years it will have been. When the mob wants to get rid of someone, the target is sent 30 years into the past, where a hired gun awaits. Joe (Joseph Gordon-Levitt) is a "looper," a hitman who eliminates these targets. However, his life becomes complicated when he is assigned to kill his future self (Bruce Willis).

title: John Wick: Chapter 2
description: Retired super-assassin John Wick (Keanu Reeves) is forced back into the criminal underworld to honor a debt owed to a former associate. This leads him to Rome, where he faces off against some of the world's deadliest killers.

title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
description: Jack Reacher (Tom Cruise) returns to his old military headquarters to meet Major Susan Turner (Cobie Smulders), only to find she has been arrested for treason. Reacher uncovers a conspiracy and must clear her name while facing a dangerous adversary.
writer: Richard Wenk, Edward Zwick, Marshall Herskovitz

title: Pacific Rim Uprising
description: Ten years after the events of the first film, Jake Pentecost (John Boyega), the son of Stacker Pentecost, teams up with rival Lambert (Scott Eastwood) and 15-year-old hacker Amara (Cailee Spaeny) to lead a new generation of Jaeger pilots. Together, they face a new threat that could end humanity.
writer: Steven S. DeKnight, Emily Carmichael, Kira Snyder, T.S. Nowlin

title: Jason Bourne
description: Jason Bourne (Matt Damon) comes out of hiding to uncover hidden truths about his past, leading him to confront a sinister network that uses terror and technology to maintain unchecked power.

title: Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle
description: Four high school students are sucked into a video game world where they transform into avatars and must work together to survive the jungle's deadly challenges and return home.
writer: Chris McKenna, Erik Sommers, Scott Rosenberg, Jeff Pinkner

title: Crazy Rich Asians
description: The story follows Rachel Chu, a Chinese-American economics professor, who travels to Singapore with her boyfriend Nick Young. She discovers that Nick is from a super-rich family, and her journey to fit in with his world of wealth and luxury becomes complicated by family expectations, cultural differences, and her own identity struggles.

title: Bad Boys for Life
description: Detectives Mike Lowrey (Will Smith) and Marcus Burnett (Martin Lawrence) reunite for a final ride when a dangerous drug lord and his son seek revenge on them, forcing them to team up with a new elite team to stop the criminals.\n
writer: Chris Bremner, Peter Craig, Joe Carnahan

title: Argo
description: An exfiltration specialist masquerades as a Hollywood producer in order to rescue six Americans who are held captive in Tehran during the US hostage crisis in Iran.\n

title: The Great Wall
description: Set in ancient China, two European mercenaries, William Garin (Matt Damon) and Pero Tovar (Pedro Pascal), are captured by the Imperial Army while searching for gunpowder. They are taken to the Great Wall, where they discover that the wall is meant to protect China from the deadly Tao Tei, monstrous creatures threatening the empire. Together, they must help defend the wall against these terrifying foes.
writer: Carlo Bernard, Doug Miro, Tony Gilroy

title: Never Let Me Go
description: Kathy H., Tommy, and Ruth grow up at Hailsham, an isolated boarding school, unaware of the dark purpose behind their lives. As they mature, they come to understand that they are clones created for the sole purpose of donating their organs. The film explores their relationships, desires, and the moral questions surrounding their fate.\n

title: 10 Cloverfield Lane
description: After surviving a car accident, Michelle (Mary Elizabeth Winstead) wakes up in an underground bunker with two men: Howard (John Goodman) and Emmett (John Gallagher Jr.). Howard insists that a catastrophic event has made the outside world uninhabitable. As Michelle becomes increasingly suspicious of Howard's motives, she begins to uncover unsettling truths about her situation, leading to a tense and thrilling escape attempt.

title: The Purge: Anarchy
description: Set in a dystopian future where the annual Purge allows all crimes to be legal for one night, the film follows Sergeant Leo Barnes (Frank Grillo) who is seeking revenge for his son’s death during the Purge. He ends up protecting a mother and daughter (Carmen Ejogo, Zach Gilford) who are stranded on the streets during the chaos. Together, they must survive the night amidst the violence and moral dilemmas of the Purge.

title: Annabelle Comes Home
description: After the terrifying events in "Annabelle: Creation," demonologists Ed and Lorraine Warren bring the cursed doll, Annabelle, to their home. They lock it away in a glass case in their artifact room, hoping to contain her malevolent powers. However, when their daughter Judy (Mckenna Grace) and her babysitter Mary Ellen (Madison Iseman) are left alone, Annabelle awakens other evil spirits, leading to a night of terror in the Warren home.\n

title: Doctor Sleep
description: Decades after the traumatic events at the Overlook Hotel, Dan Torrance (Ewan McGregor) struggles with alcoholism and his psychic abilities, known as the "shining." He finds solace working at a hospice, using his powers to comfort dying patients. However, his life takes a turn when he meets Abra Stone, a young girl with an extraordinary shine. Together, they must confront The True Knot, a sinister cult that preys on children with the shining to sustain their immortality.

title: Lootera
description: "Lootera" is a 2013 Indian romantic drama directed by Vikramaditya Motwane, featuring Ranveer Singh and Sonakshi Sinha in lead roles. The film is inspired by O. Henry's short story "The Last Leaf" and is set in 1953. It narrates the poignant tale of Pakhi, an aristocrat's daughter, who falls in love with a visiting archaeologist harboring a secret that threatens their relationship.
writer: O. Henry, Bhavani Iyer, Anurag Kashyap

title: Raanjhanaa
description: When Kundan finds that his childhood love, Zoya, likes someone from her community, he decides to forget about her. However, when he realises she is lying about her fiance's religion, he goes berserk.

title: Gehraiyaan
description: The life of Alisha, a thirty-year-old yoga instructor, is usurped by the entry of her cousin Tia's fiance, Zain. With a troubled past in common, Alisha and Zain find solace and angst in each other.
writer: Shakun Batra, Ayesha De, VitreSumit Roy

title: Shiddat
description: After falling madly in love, a man tries to convey his feelings. However, the object of his affections is betrothed to another and asks him to prove his love.
writer: Shridhar Raghavan, Dheeraj Rattan, Pooja Ladha Surti

title: Annihilation
description: A biologist joins an expedition into a mysterious quarantined zone known as "The Shimmer," where the laws of nature are distorted. As the team ventures deeper, they uncover mutated landscapes and creatures while facing psychological and existential threats.

title: Kabir singh
description: Kabir Singh, a brilliant but short-tempered surgeon, spirals into self-destruction after his girlfriend, Preeti, is forced to marry someone else. His descent involves excessive use of drugs and alcohol, leading to professional and personal challenge

title: Tanajhi
description: Set in the 17th century, the film follows Tanhaji Malusare, a military chieftain in the Maratha army under Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj. Tanhaji leads a mission to recapture the strategically important Kondhana fort from the Mughal empire, facing off against the ruthless Mughal chieftain Udaybhan Singh Rathore.

title: Darlings
description: Badrunissa "Badru" Ansari (Alia Bhatt) is married to Hamza (Vijay Varma), an alcoholic who subjects her to domestic abuse. After enduring years of violence, Badru, with the support of her mother Shamshunissa (Shefali Shah), decides to take matters into her own hands to seek revenge and reclaim her life.

title: Oh my god 2
description: Kanti Sharan Mudgal, a devout follower of Lord Shiva, faces a personal crisis when his son, Vivek, is expelled from school due to a controversial incident. Believing that misinformation and lack of proper education are to blame, Kanti embarks on a legal battle to mandate comprehensive education in schools, challenging societal norms and confronting his own beliefs.

title: Manjumel boys
description: A group of friends from Manjummel, Kerala, embark on a vacation to Kodaikanal. Their trip takes a perilous turn when one of them becomes trapped in the Guna Caves. The film chronicles their daring rescue mission, testing their unity and resilience.

title: Dhrishyam 2
description: Seven years after the events of the first film, Vijay Salgaonkar and his family are still haunted by the past. As the investigation into the missing young man is reopened, new evidence threatens to unravel Vijay's carefully constructed alibi, putting his family's safety at risk.
writer: Jeethu Joseph, Aamil Keeyan Khan, Abhishek Pathak

title: Ludo
description: From a resurfaced sex tape to a rogue suitcase of money, four wildly different stories overlap at the whims of fate, chance, and one eccentric criminal.

title: Dasvi
description: Ganga Ram Chaudhary, an uneducated and corrupt Chief Minister, is imprisoned for his involvement in a scam. While in jail, he decides to pursue his education and attempts to pass the 10th-grade examination, known as 'Dasvi'. Simultaneously, his wife, Bimla Devi, takes over his political position, leading to unexpected challenges and personal growth for both.
writer: Ritesh Shah, Suresh Nair, Sandeep Leyzell

title: The white tiger
description: Balram Halwai, an ambitious Indian driver, uses his wit and cunning to escape from poverty and rise to the top as a successful entrepreneur. The film is an epic journey based on the New York Times bestseller.

title: Avatar 2
description: Set more than a decade after the events of the first film, the story follows Jake Sully and Neytiri as they navigate life with their newfound family on Pandora. When an old threat resurfaces, they must work together with the Na'vi race to protect their home.
writer: James Cameron, Rick Jaffa, Amanda Silver

title: Baahubali: The Beginning
description: In the ancient kingdom of Mahishmati, a young man named Shivudu grows up in a remote tribal village. Driven by curiosity and a sense of adventure, he climbs a massive waterfall and discovers a new world. There, he becomes entangled in a longstanding conflict and learns about his royal lineage, leading him to confront the tyrannical ruler Bhallaladeva to rescue his imprisoned mother, Devasena.

title: Baahubali 2: The Conclusion
description: After learning about his heritage, Mahendra Baahubali (Shivudu) sets out to avenge his father's death and reclaim the kingdom of Mahishmati from the tyrannical rule of his uncle, Bhallaladeva.
writer: V. Vijayendra Prasad, S. S. Rajamouli

title: RRR
description: Set in the 1920s, "RRR" is a fictional tale that explores the journey of two Indian revolutionaries, Alluri Sitarama Raju and Komaram Bheem, who embark on a perilous mission against British colonialists. The film delves into their friendship and their fight for freedom.
cast[0].actor: N. T. Rama Rao Jr. (as Komaram Bheem)

title: Kantara
description: Set in the 1990s in a village in South Karnataka, "Kantara" follows the conflict between the villagers and the forest department over land rights. The villagers believe the land was gifted to them by their demigod protector, leading to tensions with the authorities

title: Laapataa Ladies
description: Set in rural India in 2001, the film follows the misadventures of two young brides who get lost from the same train while en route to their new homes. Through a series of mistaken identities and humorous escapades, the story explores their journey of self-discovery and the ensuing chaos.

title: Transformers: The Last Knight
description: Humans are at war with the Transformers, and Optimus Prime is gone. The key to saving the future lies buried in the secrets of the past.
writer: Art Marcum, Matt Holloway, Ken Nolan

title: Gravity
description: Dr. Ryan Stone, a medical engineer on her first shuttle mission, and veteran astronaut Matt Kowalski are on a routine spacewalk when disaster strikes. Their shuttle is destroyed, leaving them stranded in space with limited oxygen and no communication with Earth. They must work together to survive and find a way back home.

title: Oblivion
description: In the year 2077, Jack Harper is one of the last drone repairmen stationed on Earth, which has been devastated after decades of war with a terrifying threat known as the Scavs. As part of a massive operation to extract vital resources, Jack's mission is nearly complete. Living in and patrolling the skies from thousands of feet above, his existence is brought crashing down when he rescues a stranger from a downed spacecraft. Her arrival triggers a chain of events that forces Jack to question everything he knows and puts the fate of humanity in his hands.
writer: Joseph Kosinski, Karl Gajdusek, Michael Arndt

title: Prometheus
description: In 2093, archaeologists Dr. Elizabeth Shaw and Charlie Holloway lead a scientific expedition aboard the spaceship Prometheus to explore a distant moon, LV-223, following star maps found among ancient Earth cultures. They aim to discover the origins of humanity by encountering a superior extraterrestrial species known as the Engineers. However, upon arrival, the crew faces unforeseen horrors that challenge their mission and survival.

title: Edge of Tomorrow
description: In a future where Earth is under attack by an alien species known as the Mimics, Major William Cage (Tom Cruise), a public relations officer with no combat experience, is forced into a suicide mission. He is killed within minutes but finds himself caught in a time loop, reliving the same day over and over. Each death brings him closer to understanding the enemy and his own abilities, especially when he teams up with the skilled warrior Rita Vrataski (Emily Blunt).
writer: Christopher McQuarrie, Jez Butterworth, John-Henry Butterworth

title: Hereditary
description: After the death of her secretive mother, Annie Graham and her family begin to unravel cryptic and increasingly terrifying secrets about their ancestry. As they uncover more about their sinister lineage, they find themselves trying to escape the dark fate they have inherited.

title: The Cabin in the Woods
description: A group of college students retreat to a remote cabin for a weekend getaway, only to discover that they are part of a mysterious ritual controlled by unseen technicians manipulating events from an underground facility. As horrors unfold, the group must navigate a series of deadly challenges to survive.

title: The Witch
description: Set in 1630s New England, a devout Christian family is exiled from their Puritan plantation and establishes a farm on the edge of a remote forest. Soon after, their infant son mysteriously vanishes, and their crops fail. As paranoia and despair grip the family, they begin to turn on one another, suspecting that their eldest daughter, Thomasin, is practicing witchcraft, leading them into a downward spiral of fear and madness.

title: Don't Breathe
description: A trio of reckless thieves breaks into the house of a wealthy blind man, thinking they'll get away with the perfect heist. They're wrong.

title: Ouija: Origin of Evil
description: In 1967 Los Angeles, a widowed mother named Alice Zander, who works as a spiritual medium, introduces a Ouija board into her séances to enhance her scam business. Unwittingly, she invites a malevolent spirit into her home, which possesses her youngest daughter, Doris. The family must confront unthinkable fears to save Doris and send the sinister entity back to the other side.

title: Mama
description: After their parents' deaths, two young sisters vanish into the woods, leading to a frantic search. Years later, they're discovered alive in a decrepit cabin and taken in by their uncle and his girlfriend. As the girls adjust to their new life, a sinister presence they call "Mama" follows, harboring a dark attachment to them.
writer: Andy Muschietti, Barbara Muschietti, Neil Cross

title: Raat Akeli Hai
description: A small-town cop is summoned to investigate the death of a wealthy landlord on his wedding night. As he delves deeper, he uncovers a web of family secrets, lies, and deceit, making the case more complex than it initially appeared

title: Bulbbul
description: Set in the late 19th century Bengal Presidency, the film follows Bulbbul, a child bride who grows into an enigmatic woman presiding over her household. As mysterious deaths plague her village, the legend of a chudail (witch) becomes intertwined with Bulbbul's journey toward self-discovery and justice

title: Ittefaq
description: A police officer investigates a double murder case involving two witnesses, who are also the prime suspects. As he delves deeper, he uncovers conflicting versions of what transpired, leading to a complex web of deceit and mystery.
writer: Abhay Chopra, Shreyas Jain, Nikhil Mehrotra

title: Phantom
description: Following the 26/11 Mumbai attacks, India's intelligence agency orchestrates an undercover operation to eliminate the masterminds behind the assault. The mission is assigned to Daniyal Khan, a disgraced soldier seeking redemption. His journey takes him across various countries as he hunts down the perpetrators, facing numerous challenges and moral dilemmas along the way

title: A Wednesday
description: The film centers on a retiring police commissioner, Prakash Rathod, who recounts the most challenging case of his career. An anonymous caller informs him about bombs planted throughout Mumbai, demanding the release of four militants in exchange for information on the bomb locations. As the story unfolds, the film delves into themes of justice, terrorism, and the power of the common man.

title: Malang
description: The story follows Advait, a young introvert who meets the free-spirited Sara in Goa. Their love story takes a dark turn as they become entangled in a web of crime and vengeance. Years later, Advait is out for revenge, facing a ruthless police officer and a mysterious adversary.

title: The House Next Door
description: Living a peaceful life in the mountains, Krishnakanth and Lakshmi welcome their new neighbours, the D'Costas. When their eldest daughter, Jenny, invites unwanted elements in the house, terror ensues.

title: Gaslight
description: Meesha, a young woman who has been away from home for 15 years, returns to her family's royal estate to meet her estranged father. Upon arrival, she finds him missing, and as she searches for answers, she experiences eerie events that make her question reality. With the help of a loyal aide, she unravels dark secrets hidden within the mansion.\n

title: Bhediya
description: Bhaskar, a young man, travels to Arunachal Pradesh for a development project but is bitten by a mysterious wolf. Soon, he starts experiencing strange transformations, turning into a werewolf under the full moon. As he struggles to understand his new identity, his friends help him uncover the truth behind the legend of the wolf.

title: Chhorii
description: Sakshi, eight months pregnant, and her husband Hemant are forced to flee their home due to unforeseen circumstances. They find shelter in a remote house surrounded by vast sugarcane fields, inhabited by an elderly couple. Soon after, Sakshi encounters mysterious and eerie occurrences that unveil dark secrets and challenge her sanity, putting her and her unborn child's lives at risk.

title: Captain America: Brave New World
description: Sam finds himself in the middle of an international incident after meeting with President Thaddeus Ross. He must soon discover the reason behind a nefarious global plot before the true mastermind has the entire world seeing red.
writer: Rob Edwards, Malcolm Spellman, Dalan Musson

title: You're Cordially Invited
description: \nA woman planning her sister's ideal wedding and the father of a bride-to-be discover their destination weddings at a remote resort are double-booked. When both parties decide to share the small venue, chaos ensues and disaster awaits.

title: Don't Die: The Man Who Wants to Live Forever
description: The documentary provides an intimate look into Bryan Johnson's life, showcasing his rigorous health regimen known as "Project Blueprint." This program includes taking over 100 supplements daily, adhering to a strict diet and exercise routine, and undergoing various experimental medical treatments, all aimed at reversing the aging process.

title: Chhaava
description: Chhaava is a 2025 Indian Hindi-language historical action film based on the life of Maratha Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj, played by Vicky Kaushal. It is an adaptation of the Marathi novel Chhava by Shivaji Sawant.
writer: Laxman Utekar, Rishi Virmani, Kaustubh Savarkar

title: Pushpa 2: The Rule
description: Pushpa 2: The Rule" continues the saga of Pushpa Raj, portrayed by Allu Arjun, as he navigates power dynamics and rivalries in the red sandalwood smuggling underworld. The sequel delves deeper into the intense rivalry between Pushpa Raj and SP Bhanwar Singh Shekhawat, bringing back the stellar cast from the first installment.

title: Berlin
description: Set in New Delhi during the winter of 1993, "Berlin" follows the story of a deaf-mute young man arrested by the Bureau and accused of espionage. A sign language expert is brought in to interpret during the interrogation, leading him into a complex web of intelligence rivalries, deceit, and corruption, where the line between innocence and guilt becomes increasingly blurred.

title: The Girl on the Train
description: The Girl on the Train" is a mystery thriller centered on Mira Kapoor, an alcoholic and troubled divorcee who becomes entangled in a murder investigation. As she fixates on a seemingly perfect couple she observes during her daily train rides, Mira's life spirals into a complex web of deceit and danger
writer: Ribhu Dasgupta, Viddesh Malandkar, Erin Cressida Wilson

title: Guilty
description: "Guilty" is a thriller drama that delves into the complexities of a sexual assault accusation within a prestigious university. The story centers on Nanki Dutta, a songwriter whose boyfriend, VJ, is accused of rape by a fellow student, Tanu Kumar. As the narrative unfolds, Nanki navigates various versions of the incident, confronting her own biases and the societal structures that influence perceptions of truth and justice.
writer: Ruchi Narain, Kanika Dhillon, Atika Chohan

title: Arrival
description: "Arrival" is a science fiction drama that follows linguist Dr. Louise Banks, who is recruited by the U.S. Army to communicate with mysterious extraterrestrial beings that have landed on Earth. As she deciphers their complex language, she uncovers profound revelations that challenge her understanding of time, memory, and existence.

title: The Beekeeper
description: "The Beekeeper" is an action thriller that follows Adam Clay, a retired clandestine operative seeking vengeance after his close friend, Eloise Parker, falls victim to a devastating phishing scam. As Adam embarks on a relentless quest for justice, he confronts a complex web of cybercriminals and uncovers a deeper conspiracy that tests his resolve and skills.

title: Gone Girl
description: On their fifth wedding anniversary, Nick Dunne reports that his wife, Amy, has gone missing. Under pressure from the police and a growing media frenzy, Nick's portrait of a blissful union begins to crumble. Soon, his lies, deceits, and strange behavior have everyone asking the same dark question: Did Nick Dunne kill his wife?

title: Carry-On
description: Ethan Kopek, a young TSA agent, is blackmailed by a mysterious traveler into allowing a dangerous package to pass through security onto a Christmas Eve flight. As the situation escalates, Ethan must navigate the high-stakes environment to prevent a potential disaster.

title: Nightcrawler
description: "Nightcrawler" follows Lou Bloom, a driven and morally ambiguous man desperate for work, who discovers the high-speed world of L.A. crime journalism. He begins nocturnal forays across the city, filming accidents and crimes, and selling the footage to local news stations. As Lou delves deeper, his thirst for footage leads him to become an active participant in the stories he covers, blurring the line between observer and perpetrator.

title: The Killer
description: "The Killer" follows a solitary and methodical assassin who, after a botched assignment, battles his employers—and himself—on an international manhunt he insists isn't personal.

title: Twisters
description: "Twisters" serves as a standalone sequel to the 1996 film "Twister." The story follows clashing groups of storm chasers investigating a series of tornado outbreaks in Oklahoma. As they confront the fury of nature, personal dynamics and past conflicts resurface, leading to intense and thrilling encounters.

title: Plane
description: "Plane" follows commercial pilot Brodie Torrance, who, after safely landing his storm-damaged aircraft on a war-torn island, must team up with an accused murderer to rescue the passengers taken hostage by dangerous rebels.

title: Searching
description: After his 16-year-old daughter, Margot, goes missing, widowed father David Kim embarks on a desperate search to find her. With the local investigation leading nowhere, David decides to search Margot's laptop and online history to trace her digital footprints before she disappears forever.

title: Phir Hera Pheri
description: After acquiring wealth, Raju, Shyam, and Baburao enjoy a lavish lifestyle. Seeking to double their riches, they fall victim to a scam orchestrated by a con woman named Anuradha. Left penniless and indebted to a ruthless gangster, the trio embarks on a series of comedic misadventures to repay the loan and restore their fortunes.

title: Jaane Jaan
description: "Jaane Jaan" is a mystery thriller that follows a single mother and her daughter who become entangled in a crime. Their neighbor, a gifted mathematics teacher, assists them in covering it up, all while a relentless police investigation unfolds.

title: Kho Gaye Hum Kahan
description: "Kho Gaye Hum Kahan" is a coming-of-age drama that explores the lives of three close friends—Ahana, Imaad, and Neil—navigating their twenties in Mumbai. The film delves into themes of friendship, love, ambition, and the pervasive influence of social media on modern relationships.
writer: Arjun Varain Singh, Zoya Akhtar, Reema Kagti, Yash Sahai

title: Anyone but You
description: After an amazing first date, Bea and Ben's fiery attraction turns ice-cold—until they find themselves unexpectedly reunited at a destination wedding in Australia. To navigate the awkward situation, they decide to pretend to be a couple.

title: Knives Out
description: "Knives Out" is a modern mystery where renowned detective Benoit Blanc investigates the death of celebrated novelist Harlan Thrombey. After Harlan is found dead at his estate, Blanc sifts through a web of red herrings and self-serving lies to uncover the truth behind the patriarch's untimely demise.

title: No Hard Feelings
description: Maddie Barker, a 32-year-old Uber driver and bartender in Montauk, New York, faces financial ruin after her car is repossessed. Desperate to save her inherited home, she responds to a Craigslist ad from wealthy parents seeking someone to date their introverted 19-year-old son, Percy, before he heads to Princeton University. As Maddie attempts to bring Percy out of his shell, unexpected complications arise, leading to humorous and heartfelt moments that challenge both of their perceptions about life and relationships.
genre: Sex Comedy, Raunchy Comedy, Teen Romance, Comedy, Romance, Romantic Comedy

title: The Gorge
description: "The Gorge" is a science fiction romantic action film that follows two elite snipers, Levi and Drasa, assigned to guard opposite sides of a mysterious and classified gorge. Despite strict orders to maintain distance, they develop a connection through notes and binoculars. As they confront the enigmatic threats emerging from the gorge, their bond deepens, leading to unforeseen consequences.

title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
description: The film recounts the adventures of Monsieur Gustave H., a legendary concierge at a famous European hotel between the wars, and Zero Moustafa, the lobby boy who becomes his most trusted friend. The story involves the theft and recovery of a priceless Renaissance painting, a battle for a family fortune, and the shifting political landscape of 20th-century Europe. As Gustave and Zero navigate a world of intrigue, betrayal, and romance, their bond is tested in ways neither could have anticipated.

title: The Nice Guys
description: Set in 1977 Los Angeles, "The Nice Guys" follows private eye Holland March and enforcer Jackson Healy as they team up to investigate the disappearance of a teenage girl named Amelia. Their inquiry uncovers a conspiracy involving the death of a porn star, leading them through a web of intrigue and danger.

title: Train to Busan
description: During a sudden zombie outbreak in South Korea, passengers aboard a high-speed train race to Busan—the country’s last safe haven—as they struggle to survive the relentless onslaught.

title: Jerry Maguire
description: Sports agent Jerry Maguire experiences a moral crisis, leading him to start his own agency. With only one client and a single colleague, he embarks on a journey of self-discovery and redemption.

title: Run Lola Run
description: Lola receives a frantic call from her boyfriend, Manni, who has misplaced 100,000 Deutsche Marks belonging to a crime boss. With only 20 minutes to recover the money, Lola embarks on a high-stakes race through Berlin, with the film exploring three different scenarios based on her split-second decisions.

title: What Dreams May Come
description: After dying in a car accident, Dr. Chris Nielsen (Robin Williams) navigates the afterlife, discovering a Heaven inspired by his wife's paintings. When his wife, Annie (Annabella Sciorra), succumbs to despair and takes her own life, Chris embarks on a perilous journey through Hell to rescue her soul and reunite for eternity.

title: Groundhog Day
description: Phil Connors, a cynical television weatherman, finds himself reliving the same day—February 2nd—in Punxsutawney, Pennsylvania, repeatedly. Trapped in a time loop, he embarks on a journey of self-discovery, gradually transforming from a self-centered individual to someone who embraces the value of life and personal growth.

title: The Lake House
description: Dr. Kate Forster (Sandra Bullock) and architect Alex Wyler (Keanu Reeves) both live in the same lakeside house, but two years apart. They begin exchanging letters through the house's mysterious mailbox and form a romantic connection, despite the time gap. As they unravel the mystery behind their extraordinary correspondence, they strive to meet in the same timeline.

title: The Holiday
description: Two women, Amanda Woods (Cameron Diaz) from Los Angeles and Iris Simpkins (Kate Winslet) from England, seek to escape their romantic troubles by swapping homes during the Christmas holiday. As they settle into their new surroundings, both find unexpected romance and discover fresh perspectives on life and love.

title: Charlie and the Chocolate Factory
description: Young Charlie Bucket wins a contest, allowing him and four other children to tour the magical and mysterious chocolate factory owned by the eccentric Willy Wonka.

title: A Beautiful Mind
description: The film portrays the life of John Nash, a brilliant mathematician who made significant contributions to game theory. It follows his journey from his early days at Princeton University, through his struggles with schizophrenia, and his eventual recognition with the Nobel Prize in Economics.

title: Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind
description: After a painful breakup, Joel Barish (Jim Carrey) discovers that his ex-girlfriend, Clementine Kruczynski (Kate Winslet), has undergone a procedure to erase all memories of their relationship. Heartbroken, Joel decides to undergo the same procedure. However, as his memories of Clementine begin to fade, he realizes he still loves her and attempts to preserve his memories of her before they are lost forever.

title: Barbie
description: Barbie and Ken are living in the seemingly perfect world of Barbieland. However, when they get a chance to venture into the real world, they soon discover the joys and challenges of living among humans.

title: Sin City: A Dame to Kill For
description: In the dark, crime-ridden streets of Sin City, various stories of revenge, betrayal, and redemption unfold. Dwight McCarthy (Josh Brolin) is drawn back into the life of his former lover, Ava Lord (Eva Green), who seeks his help to escape her abusive marriage. Meanwhile, gambler Johnny (Joseph Gordon-Levitt) challenges the wrong man in a high-stakes game, and Nancy Callahan (Jessica Alba) struggles with the loss of John Hartigan (Bruce Willis) as she plots her revenge against Senator Roark (Powers Boothe).

title: Kung Fu Hustle
description: Set in 1940s Shanghai, the story follows Sing, a small-time crook aspiring to join the notorious Axe Gang. His attempts to extort residents of Pigsty Alley inadvertently lead to a showdown between the gang and the slum's unlikely heroes—three martial arts masters disguised as ordinary residents. As chaos ensues, Sing discovers his true potential in the world of kung fu.
writer: Stephen Chow, Huo Xin, Chan Man-keung, Tsang Kan-cheung

title: Matilda
description: Matilda Wormwood is an exceptionally intelligent girl whose talents are overlooked by her negligent parents and oppressive school principal, Miss Trunchbull. Discovering she has telekinetic powers, Matilda uses her abilities to stand up against the injustices in her life and to help her kind-hearted teacher, Miss Honey.

title: Inside Out 1
description: film follows 11-year-old Riley, who is uprooted from her Midwest life when her father starts a new job in San Francisco. Guided by her five personified emotions—Joy, Sadness, Fear, Anger, and Disgust—Riley navigates the challenges of adjusting to a new city, house, and school.
writer: Pete Docter, Meg LeFauve, Josh Cooley

title: The Greatest Showman
description: The Greatest Showman is a musical drama inspired by the life of P.T. Barnum. It follows his journey from humble beginnings to creating the renowned Barnum & Bailey Circus, celebrating the birth of show business and the sense of wonder it inspired.

title: Coco
description: Coco follows 12-year-old Miguel, an aspiring musician born into a family with a generations-old ban on music. Desperate to prove his talent, Miguel finds himself in the Land of the Dead, where he seeks the help of his great-great-grandfather to return to the living and lift his family's ban on music.

title: Minions
description: The story follows Minions Stuart, Kevin, and Bob as they are recruited by Scarlet Overkill, a supervillain who, alongside her inventor husband Herb, hatches a plot to take over the world

title: Minions: The Rise of Gru
description: Set in the 1970s, the film follows 11-year-old Gru, who dreams of becoming the world's greatest supervillain. With the help of his loyal Minions, Gru devises a plan to join the notorious supervillain group, the Vicious 6, after they oust their leader, Wild Knuckles. However, things take a turn when Gru and his Minions find themselves on the run, leading to an unexpected mentorship with Wild Knuckles himself.

title: The Rise of The Guardians
description: When the evil spirit Pitch Black threatens to engulf the world in darkness, the Immortal Guardians—Santa Claus (North), the Easter Bunny (Bunnymund), the Tooth Fairy (Tooth), and the Sandman—recruit a new member, Jack Frost. Together, they must protect the hopes, beliefs, and imaginations of children all around the world.

title: Bird Box
description: In a post-apocalyptic world, Malorie Hayes and her two children must navigate through a forest and river blindfolded to avoid supernatural entities that cause people who look at them to commit suicide.

title: The Fault in Our Stars
description: Hazel Grace Lancaster, a sixteen-year-old cancer patient, is forced by her parents to attend a support group where she meets Augustus "Gus" Waters, a fellow cancer patient. The two form a deep bond and embark on a journey to meet Hazel's favorite author, exploring themes of love, loss, and the meaning of life.

title: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani
description: The film follows Naina Talwar, a shy and introverted medical student, who reunites with her old classmates, including the free-spirited Bunny (Kabir Thapar), on a trekking trip. As Naina opens up to new experiences, she develops feelings for Bunny, who dreams of traveling the world. Their journey explores love, friendship, and self-discovery.\n

title: Dil Toh Pagal Hain
description: Rahul, the choreographer of a successful dance troupe, does not believe in true love until he finds himself caught in a love triangle between his best friend Nisha and the dreamy Pooja. As the story unfolds, destiny plays its part in bringing true love to the stage.
writer: Tanuja Chandra, Aditya Chopra, Pamela Chopra

title: Dear Zindagi
description: Kaira, a young and ambitious cinematographer, struggles with personal and professional insecurities. She meets Dr. Jehangir "Jug" Khan, an unconventional therapist, who helps her navigate life's challenges and find new perspectives on happiness and self-acceptance.

title: Barfi
description: Set in the 1970s, the film follows Murphy "Barfi" Johnson, a deaf and mute yet lively and charming young man from Darjeeling. His life takes a turn when he falls in love with Shruti, a woman from a conventional background. Later, he forms a deep bond with Jhilmil, an autistic woman. Through their journey, Barfi! explores themes of unconditional love, friendship, and the pursuit of happiness beyond societal norms.

title: Padmaavat
description: Based on the epic poem Padmavat by Malik Muhammad Jayasi, Padmaavat tells the story of Rani Padmavati, a legendary Rajput queen known for her beauty, intelligence, and valor. When Sultan Alauddin Khilji becomes obsessed with her and wages war to claim her, she and her husband, Maharawal Ratan Singh, must defend their kingdom and honor. The film explores themes of love, sacrifice, and Rajput bravery.

title: Sanju
description: Sanju is a biographical drama based on the life of Bollywood actor Sanjay Dutt. The film chronicles his rise to stardom, struggles with drug addiction, time in prison under the Arms Act, and his relationship with his father, Sunil Dutt. Through humor, drama, and emotional depth, the film explores the many ups and downs in the actor’s controversial life.

title: Kedarnath
description: Kedarnath is a romantic drama set against the backdrop of the devastating 2013 Uttarakhand floods. The film follows the love story of Mansoor, a humble Muslim porter, and Mukku, a rebellious Hindu girl from a wealthy family. As their interfaith romance blossoms, they must navigate societal pressures and an impending natural disaster that threatens to separate them forever.

title: Zero
description: Zero is a romantic drama that follows Bauua Singh, a short-statured man from Meerut, as he navigates complex relationships with Aafia Bhinder, a scientist with cerebral palsy, and Babita Kumari, a Bollywood superstar. The film explores themes of love, self-discovery, and acceptance.

title: Mission Mangal
description: Mission Mangal is a space drama based on the true story of India's Mars Orbiter Mission (Mangalyaan), spearheaded by ISRO scientists. The film follows a dedicated team of scientists who overcome various personal and professional challenges to successfully launch India’s first interplanetary mission.
writer: Jagan Shakti, R. Balki, Nidhi Singh Dharma, Saketh Kondiparthi

title: Dream Girl
description: Karamveer "Karam" Singh, known for his ability to mimic female voices, takes up a job at a "friendship" call center, posing as "Pooja." His enchanting voice attracts a host of admirers, leading to comical and chaotic situations as he juggles his double life.

title: Bala
description: Bala follows the story of Balmukund "Bala" Shukla, a young man from Kanpur who struggles with premature baldness. Once a confident, charming person, his receding hairline shatters his self-esteem. The film humorously yet thoughtfully explores beauty standards, self-acceptance, and society's obsession with appearances.

title: The Sky Is Pink
description: The film chronicles the 25-year love story of Aditi and Niren Chaudhary, spanning from their early romance to the trials they face as parents. Their daughter, Aisha, born with a rare genetic disorder, becomes the central figure, narrating their journey from her perspective after her death. The story delves into themes of love, resilience, and the complexities of coping with terminal illness within a family.

title: Shubh Mangal Zyada Saavdhan
description: The film centers on Kartik Singh and Aman Tripathi, a gay couple deeply in love. Their journey to gain acceptance hits a roadblock when they confront Aman's conservative family in Allahabad. The narrative humorously yet poignantly addresses the challenges of coming out, societal norms, and the essence of love transcending traditional boundaries.

title: Thappad
description: Amrita's seemingly perfect life is shattered when her husband, Vikram, slaps her during a party. This singular act of violence compels her to reassess her marriage and her own identity. Despite societal pressure to overlook the incident, Amrita decides to file for divorce, challenging deep-seated patriarchal values and asserting her right to respect and dignity.

title: Shakuntala Devi
description: The film chronicles the extraordinary journey of Shakuntala Devi, a world-renowned mathematician known as the "human computer." Beyond her mathematical genius, the story explores her personal life, particularly her complex relationship with her daughter, Anupama. The narrative highlights her struggles and triumphs as a mother and a woman ahead of her time.

title: Gunjan Saxena: The Kargil Girl
description: The film chronicles the inspiring journey of Gunjan Saxena, who, driven by her childhood dream of becoming a pilot, overcomes societal and familial challenges to join the Indian Air Force. Her determination leads her to serve as a helicopter pilot during the 1999 Kargil War, making significant contributions and paving the way for future generations of women in the armed forces.

title: Panga
description: Jaya Nigam, once a celebrated Kabaddi player, now leads a life balancing her duties as a railway reservation clerk, wife, and mother. Encouraged by her supportive husband, Prashant, and their spirited son, Adi, Jaya confronts societal expectations and personal challenges to return to the sport she loves. With the assistance of her friend and former teammate, Meenu, Jaya embarks on a journey to reclaim her position in the national Kabaddi team, redefining her identity beyond traditional roles.

title: Sooryavanshi
description: DCP Veer Sooryavanshi, the chief of Mumbai's Anti-Terrorism Squad, uncovers a plot by a terrorist group planning attacks in the city. As he races against time to prevent the attacks, he collaborates with DCP Bajirao Singham and Inspector Sangram Bhalerao, leading to high-octane action sequences and a gripping narrative.

title: Bunty Aur Babli 2
description: Bunty Aur Babli 2 is a sequel to the 2005 hit Bunty Aur Babli. The story follows Rakesh and Vimmi, the original con artists who have now settled into a normal life. However, their quiet existence is disrupted when a new, younger duo starts using their name to pull off high-profile scams across India. This forces the original Bunty and Babli out of retirement to reclaim their identity and stop the imposters. The film is a fun-filled crime comedy packed with wit, humor, and stylish cons.

title: Antim: The Final Truth
description: Antim: The Final Truth is an action-packed crime drama that follows the intense battle between a righteous Sikh police officer, Rajveer Singh (played by Salman Khan), and a young, ambitious gangster, Rahuliya (played by Aayush Sharma). The film highlights themes of power, corruption, and survival as Rahuliya rises through the ranks of the underworld while clashing with Rajveer, who is determined to bring justice. The movie is an adaptation of the Marathi film Mulshi Pattern.
writer: Mahesh Manjrekar, Abhijeet Deshpande, Siddharth Salvi

title: Mimi
description: Set in a small town in Rajasthan, the story follows Mimi (Kriti Sanon), an aspiring actress who agrees to become a surrogate mother for an American couple in exchange for ₹2 million. However, when the couple backs out, Mimi faces unexpected challenges, leading to a transformative journey of self-discovery and motherhood.

title: BellBottom
description: BellBottom is an action thriller inspired by true events from the 1980s. The story follows RAW agent Anshul Malhotra, codenamed "BellBottom" (played by Akshay Kumar), who is assigned to a covert mission to rescue hostages from a hijacked Indian plane. The film showcases his intelligence, strategic planning, and execution of a daring rescue operation.

title: Roohi
description: Roohi is a horror-comedy that follows two small-town men, Bhawra and Kattanni, who are hired to kidnap a bride. However, things take a bizarre turn when they discover that the woman, Roohi, is possessed by a spirit named Afza. What follows is a series of eerie yet hilarious events as they try to deal with the supernatural entity while navigating their own growing feelings for Roohi.

title: Toofaan
description: Toofaan follows Aziz Ali, a street thug from Mumbai who discovers his passion for boxing. Encouraged by his love interest, Dr. Ananya, he takes up the sport under the mentorship of the disciplined coach Nana Prabhu. However, his journey is filled with challenges, including societal barriers and personal struggles. The film explores his transformation from a goon to a determined boxer fighting against all odds.

title: Joker: Folie à Deux
description: In this musical sequel to "Joker" (2019), Arthur Fleck (Joaquin Phoenix) is incarcerated in Arkham Asylum, where he meets Harley Quinn (Lady Gaga), a fellow patient. Their shared delusions lead them into a twisted romance, intertwining performances of iconic American pop songs, reflecting a darker, unorthodox take on the American dream.

title: The Crow
description: In this reboot, Eric Draven and his fiancée, Shelly Webster, are murdered by a crime syndicate. Resurrected by a mystical crow, Eric embarks on a quest for vengeance against those responsible for their deaths.

title: Gladiator II
description: Gladiator II" follows Lucius Verus Aurelius, the exiled Prince of Rome, who becomes a prisoner of war and fights as a gladiator under Macrinus, a former slave plotting to overthrow the twin emperors Geta and Caracalla.
writer: David Scarpa, Peter Craig, David Scarpa

title: Abigail
description: A group of kidnappers abducts 12-year-old ballerina Abigail, the daughter of a powerful underworld figure, and demands a $50 million ransom. Unbeknownst to them, Abigail is a vampire who orchestrated the kidnapping for her own amusement, leading to a night of terror as the captors become her prey.

title: Tarot
description: Based on the 1992 novel "Horrorscope" by Nicholas Adams, "Tarot" follows a group of college students who, after using a mysterious Tarot deck, begin to experience gruesome deaths one by one.

title: A Quiet Place: Day One
description: Set in New York City, the film follows Samira, a terminally ill woman, during the early stages of an invasion by blind, extraterrestrial creatures with an acute sense of hearing. As chaos ensues, Samira must navigate the perilous urban landscape to survive.

title: Captain America: Brave New World
description: Sam Wilson, having assumed the mantle of Captain America, meets with newly elected U.S. President Thaddeus Ross. Following their meeting, Sam finds himself entangled in an international incident and must uncover the motives behind a nefarious global plot before the mastermind plunges the world into chaos.

title: Maharaj
description: Based on the Maharaj Libel Case of 1862, the film follows a bold journalist who challenges the immoral behavior of a revered religious leader, leading to a landmark legal battle that questions societal norms and the abuse of power

title: Jigra
description: Satya, a savvy and lethal fixer working in her powerful relatives' luxury hotel, embarks on a mission to save her brother Ankur, who has been framed for a drug-related crime and sentenced to death in the fictional nation of Hanshi Dao. Teaming up with a former mob boss and an ex-cop seeking redemption, Satya navigates a perilous path to rescue Ankur before it's too late.

title: Ulajh
description: The film follows the journey of a young diplomat from a prominent family of patriots who becomes entangled in a perilous personal conspiracy while serving in a career-defining post abroad.

title: Savi
description: Savi, a simple housewife, undertakes a daring mission to break her husband out of one of England's high-security prisons, facing numerous challenges and dangers along the way.

title: Back in Action
description: Former CIA spies Emily and Matt are pulled back into espionage after their secret identities are exposed.​

title: Carry-On
description: A young TSA agent is blackmailed by a mysterious traveler into allowing a dangerous package onto a Christmas Eve flight, leading to a tense and high-stakes scenario

title: The Witcher: Sirens of the Deep
description: Mutant monster hunter Geralt of Rivia is hired to investigate attacks in a seaside village, uncovering an ancient conflict between humans and merpeople that threatens to ignite a war between kingdoms. With the aid of allies, Geralt must resolve the mystery before hostilities escalate.

title: Unstoppable
description: Unstoppable" tells the inspiring true story of Anthony Robles, who was born with one leg but defied the odds to become an NCAA Division I wrestling champion. The film follows his journey of perseverance, highlighting the unwavering support of his mother, Judy, and the challenges he overcomes to achieve his dreams.
writer: Eric Champnella, Alex Harris, John Hindman

title: Be Happy
description: Be Happy" is a heartwarming dance drama that follows the journey of a single father and his witty, wise-beyond-her-years daughter. When his daughter's dream of performing in the country's biggest dance reality show collides with a life-altering crisis, the father is driven to do the unthinkable, showcasing the extraordinary lengths he will go to fulfill her wishes and find happiness
writer: Remo D'Souza, Chirag Garg, Tushar Hiranandani, Kanishka Singh De

title: Sikandar
description: Sikandar follows Sanjay "Sikandar" Rajkot, the king of Rajkot, Gujarat, who becomes a target for Minister Rakesh Pradhan after killing his son. When his wife’s donated organs save three lives, Rakesh seeks revenge, forcing Sanjay to protect them.​

title: The Diplomat
description: Based on true events, "The Diplomat" follows Indian diplomat J.P. Singh as he endeavors to repatriate Uzma Ahmed, an Indian woman who was allegedly deceived and forced into marriage in Pakistan. The narrative delves into the complexities of international diplomacy and the personal challenges faced during the mission.

title: Superboys of Malegaon
description: The film follows Nasir Shaikh, a wedding videographer in Malegaon, who, driven by his passion for cinema, assembles a group of friends to produce a film for their community. Their journey highlights the challenges and triumphs of grassroots filmmaking, emphasizing themes of friendship, ambition, and the transformative power of storytelling.

title: Deva
description: A skilled but defiant police officer investigates a major case. The officer discovers layers of lies and betrayal during the investigation

title: Badass Ravikumar
description: Set in 1989, the story follows Ravi Kumar, a rogue cop determined to eradicate corruption and take down the baddies. Suspended for his politically incorrect methods, he is unofficially sent to Muscat to retrieve a camera reel containing sensitive information about Indian secret agents. This intel is being pursued by Syed Bashir, Carlos Pedro, and Laila, while Commissioner Awasthi entrusts Ravi with the mission.
writer: Kushal Ved Bakshi, Bunty Rathore, Himesh Reshammiya​

title: Fateh
description: Ex-Special Ops officer Fateh Singh springs back to action when a girl falls prey to a cybercrime syndicate. Racing against time, can he bring down the mafia?

title: Azaad
description: Set against the backdrop of 1920 during the pre-Independence era, "Azaad" portrays the struggles of villagers oppressed by the cruel Zamindari system. The story follows Govind, a poor stable boy who dreams of owning his own horse, as he confronts the atrocities of the tyrannical Rai Bahadur and his son Tej.
writer: Chandan Arora, Abhishek Kapoor, Suresh Nair

title: The Amateur
description: Charlie Heller, a brilliant but introverted CIA cryptographer, is devastated when his wife is killed in a London terrorist attack. When his superiors refuse to act, he blackmails them into providing field training, embarking on a global mission to avenge her death.​

title: Dhoom Dhaam
