description: Newlyweds Koyal (Yami Gautam Dhar) and Veer (Pratik Gandhi) find their wedding night turned upside down when armed intruders storm in. Mistaken identities and a mysterious figure named "Charlie" propel the couple into a thrilling chase, dodging goons and police alike.
writer: Aditya Dhar, Rishab Seth, Aarsh Vora

title: I Want to Talk
description: Arjun Sen, a successful marketing executive in California, faces a life-altering diagnosis of laryngeal cancer, leading to multiple surgeries and a prognosis of only 100 days to live. As he grapples with his illness, Arjun strives to mend his strained relationship with his daughter, Reya, and finds solace in unexpected friendships. The film explores themes of resilience, familial bonds, and the human spirit's capacity to find hope amidst adversity.

title: Hisaab Barabar
description: Radhe Mohan Sharma, a diligent railway ticket examiner and self-proclaimed accounts expert, discovers a minor discrepancy in his bank account. His pursuit to rectify this leads him into a vast financial fraud orchestrated by influential banker Micky Mehta. As Radhe delves deeper, he confronts systemic corruption, facing personal and moral dilemmas.
writer: Ashwni Dhir, Purva Naresh, Ritesh Shastri, Dolphy Fernandes

title: Vanvaas
description: Set against the backdrop of Varanasi, Vanvaas is a poignant family drama that explores the relationship between an aging father, suffering from dementia, and his family. The film delves into themes of love, regret, and redemption, portraying the emotional journey of a family torn apart by conflicts and their path to rediscover unity amidst adversity.
writer: Anil Sharma, Amjad Ali, Sunil Sirvaiya

title: Mrs.
description: Mrs. is a Hindi-language drama film directed by Arati Kadav. It is an official remake of the Malayalam film The Great Indian Kitchen. The story follows Richa Sharma, a trained dancer who, after marriage, finds herself confined to household chores and struggles to reclaim her identity amid societal expectations.

title: Agni
description: Set in Mumbai, Agni follows Vitthalrao Surve, a dedicated fire station chief, and his brother-in-law Samit Sawant, a police inspector. As the city faces a series of mysterious fires, the duo must overcome personal differences to uncover the truth behind the arson attacks and protect their community.

title: Sikandar Ka Muqaddar
description: After a high-profile diamond heist remains unsolved, a determined police officer's pursuit of his prime suspect turns into an all-consuming obsession, leading to a gripping confrontation between duty and personal vendetta.

title: Yo Yo Honey Singh: Famous
description: This intimate documentary traces the rise, fall, and comeback of Indian rapper Yo Yo Honey Singh, delving into his journey from humble beginnings to stardom, the challenges he faced, and his return to the music scene.

title: Picture This
description: Struggling photographer Pia (Simone Ashley) receives a prediction that true love and career success await her in the next five dates she goes on. With her sister's wedding approaching and her family playing matchmaker, Pia's ex-boyfriend Charlie (Hero Fiennes Tiffin) reappears, throwing her love and professional life into chaos.

title: Companion
description: Companion is a sci-fi thriller that follows Iris (Sophie Thatcher), who embarks on a weekend getaway with her boyfriend Josh (Jack Quaid) and friends at a remote cabin. The trip takes a dark turn when it's revealed that Iris is not human but a subservient android built for human companionship. As tensions rise, Iris must fight for control and selfhood in a battle for survival.

title: Anora
description: Anora is a modern-day Cinderella story that follows Ani, a young sex worker from Brooklyn, who impulsively marries Vanya, the son of a Russian oligarch. Their whirlwind romance faces challenges when Vanya's parents attempt to annul the marriage, leading to a wild chase through New York City.

title: Wolf Man
description: Wolf Man is a modern reimagining of the classic Universal monster tale. The film follows Blake Lovell, a writer who moves his wife, Charlotte, and daughter, Ginger, to his remote childhood home in rural Oregon after inheriting it. Their attempt at a fresh start quickly turns into a nightmare when a brutal animal attack forces them to barricade inside the house. As the night progresses, Blake's injuries from the attack worsen, and he begins to exhibit increasingly monstrous behavior, leading to a terrifying transformation.

title: Plankton: The Movie
description: When Plankton's latest evil scheme is thwarted, Bikini Bottom and the surface world become threatened by an unexpected danger. Now, before Plankton can take over the world, he's going to have to save it.

title: Nickel Boys
description: Nickel Boys is a historical drama based on Colson Whitehead's Pulitzer Prize-winning novel. Set in 1960s Jim Crow-era Florida, the film follows Elwood Curtis, a bright African-American teenager whose aspirations are derailed when he's unjustly sent to Nickel Academy, a brutal reform school. There, he forms a bond with Turner, a fellow inmate with a more cynical outlook. Together, they navigate the harrowing realities of institutional abuse and systemic racism. The film employs a first-person perspective to immerse viewers in Elwood's experience, offering a poignant exploration of resilience and friendship amidst adversity.
writer: RaMell Ross, Joslyn Barnes, Colson Whitehead

title: Salem's Lot
description: Salem's Lot is a supernatural horror film based on Stephen King's 1975 novel. The story follows author Ben Mears, who returns to his childhood hometown of Jerusalem's Lot seeking inspiration for his next book. Upon arrival, he discovers that the town is being preyed upon by a bloodthirsty vampire. As the vampire's influence spreads, Mears must confront the evil threatening the town and its inhabitants.

title: Kesari Chapter 2: The Untold Story of Jallianwala Bagh​
description: Set in the early 20th century, the film portrays the courageous legal battle led by Justice C. Sankaran Nair against the British Empire following the Jallianwala Bagh massacre. With the assistance of young advocate Dilreet Gill, Nair challenges the British authorities, seeking justice and exposing the atrocities committed during the colonial era.​
writer: Karan Singh Tyagi, Amritpal Singh Bindra, Akshat Ghildial, Sumit Saxena​

title: iHostage
description: Inspired by the real-life 2022 hostage crisis at Amsterdam's Apple Store, iHostage follows Ilian, a Bulgarian man who becomes entangled in a life-threatening situation when an armed assailant takes the store's occupants hostage. The film presents a tense and emotional narrative through the perspectives of the attacker, the hostages, and the first responders, highlighting courage, survival, and the lasting impact of terror.​

title: Raid 2
description: In Raid 2, IRS officer Amay Patnaik returns to undertake his 75th raid, targeting the influential Dada Manohar Bhai. As he delves deeper into the world of white-collar crime, Amay faces formidable challenges that test his resolve and commitment to justice.
writer: Ritesh Shah, Raj Kumar Gupta, Jaideep Yadav, Karan Vyas

title: Sinners
description: Set in 1932 Mississippi, twin brothers Smoke and Stack return to their hometown to start anew by opening a juke joint. Their plans are upended when a vampire named Remmick arrives, leading to a confrontation that intertwines themes of music, race, and supernatural horror.

title: Thunderbolts*
description: In ​Thunderbolts*​, a group of antiheroes—including Yelena Belova, Bucky Barnes, Red Guardian, Ghost, Taskmaster, and John Walker—are assembled by CIA Director Valentina Allegra de Fontaine for a covert mission. However, they soon discover they've been manipulated into a deadly trap. Forced to confront their troubled pasts and work together, they face off against a powerful superhuman threat known as the Sentry, whose unstable alter ego, the Void, poses a global danger.
writer: Eric Pearson, Joanna Calo, Lee Sung Jin

title: A Minecraft Movie
description: In A Minecraft Movie, four misfits—Garrett "The Garbage Man" Garrison, Henry, Natalie, and Dawn—are transported through a portal into the Overworld, a cubic wonderland that thrives on imagination. To return home, they must master their new environment and embark on a magical quest with the help of an expert crafter named Steve.
writer: Chris Bowman, Hubbel Palmer, Neil Widener, Gavin James, Chris Galletta

title: The Accountant 2
description: In The Accountant 2, Christian Wolff (Ben Affleck), a brilliant but socially challenged accountant, is drawn back into a dangerous world when an old acquaintance is murdered, leaving behind a cryptic message: "Find the accountant." Teaming up with his estranged brother Braxton (Jon Bernthal) and Treasury agent Marybeth Medina (Cynthia Addai-Robinson), Christian uncovers a deadly conspiracy involving a mysterious woman named Anaïs and her missing son. As they delve deeper, they confront a network of killers determined to keep their secrets buried.

title: Rust
description: Set in 1880s Kansas, Rust follows Harland Rust (Alec Baldwin), a seasoned outlaw with a bounty on his head, who comes out of hiding to rescue his 13-year-old grandson, Lucas Hollister (Patrick Scott McDermott), from execution after an accidental killing. Together, they flee across the American frontier, pursued by U.S. Marshal Wood Helm (Josh Hopkins) and relentless bounty hunter Fenton "Preacher" Lang (Travis Fimmel).

title: Until Dawn
description: One year after her sister Melanie mysteriously disappeared, Clover and her friends venture into the remote valley where she vanished, seeking answers. Exploring an abandoned visitor center, they find themselves stalked by a masked killer and horrifically murdered one by one... only to wake up and find themselves back at the beginning of ... repeatedly—each time facing a different, more terrifying threat. With hope dwindling, the group realizes they have a limited number.

title: The Surfer
description: In The Surfer, an unnamed man (Nicolas Cage) returns to his childhood beach in Australia with his teenage son, intending to surf and reclaim his family's former home. However, their plans are disrupted by a group of territorial locals known as the "Bay Boys," led by the enigmatic Scally (Julian McMahon). As tensions escalate, the protagonist finds himself drawn into a psychological and physical conflict that challenges his identity and sanity.

title: Warfare
description: Warfare is a visceral, boots-on-the-ground story of modern warfare, told like never before: in real time and based on the memory of the people who lived it. The film embeds audiences with a platoon of American Navy SEALs in the home of an Iraqi family, overwatching the movement of US forces through insurgent territory.

title: Limitless
description: Limitless follows Eddie Morra, a struggling writer who discovers NZT-48, a mysterious nootropic drug that unlocks his brain's full potential. As he experiences unprecedented success, he attracts the attention of powerful forces and faces dangerous side effects.

title: Havoc
description: After a drug deal goes awry, bruised detective Walker (Tom Hardy) must navigate a corrupt city's criminal underworld to rescue a politician's estranged son. As he delves deeper, he uncovers a web of corruption and conspiracy that threatens to engulf the entire city.

title: Last Bullet
description: In Last Bullet, car genius Lino returns to conclude his vendetta against Areski and the corrupt commander who ruined their lives.

title: Heart Eyes
description: Set in Seattle during Valentine's Day, Heart Eyes follows Ally McCabe, a pitch designer, and Jay Simmonds, a consulting advertiser, who are mistaken for a couple by the infamous Heart Eyes Killer—a masked murderer targeting romantic pairs. As they navigate a series of harrowing events, they uncover a chilling conspiracy involving multiple perpetrators, leading to a deadly confrontation that tests their survival and burgeoning relationship.
writer: Phillip Murphy, Christopher Landon, Michael Kennedy

title: The Electric State
description: Set in an alternate 1990s America, The Electric State follows Michelle, an orphaned teenager, who embarks on a journey across a dystopian landscape with a mysterious robot named Cosmo to find her long-lost brother. Along the way, they are joined by Keats, an eccentric drifter. As they traverse the American West, they uncover a conspiracy involving a powerful tech corporation, SENTRE Technologies, which has sequestered surviving rebel robots in an exclusion zone known as "the electric state."

title: Nonnas
description: Inspired by the true story of Joe Scaravella, Nonnas follows Joe (Vince Vaughn), a Staten Island native who, after the loss of his mother and grandmother, finds solace in their traditional recipes. He opens an Italian restaurant, Enoteca Maria, staffed entirely by grandmothers ("nonnas") from various Italian regions. As the nonnas bring their unique flavors and personalities to the kitchen, Joe navigates challenges in honoring his family's legacy and building a community around food and love.

title: Mission: Impossible - The Final Reckoning
description: In this climactic installment, IMF agent Ethan Hunt (Tom Cruise) and his team confront a rogue AI known as "The Entity," which threatens global security by manipulating digital networks. As the world teeters on the brink of chaos, Hunt must retrieve a critical key from a sunken Russian submarine to neutralize the AI. The mission propels him into high-stakes confrontations, including daring underwater escapades and aerial stunts, culminating in a final showdown that tests his limits and the very essence of his mission.

title: Fear Street: Prom Queen
description: Set in 1988, Fear Street: Prom Queen follows the students of Shadyside High as prom season approaches. The school's popular "It Girls" are fiercely competing for the prom queen crown. However, when a gutsy outsider is unexpectedly nominated, the other candidates begin to vanish mysteriously, leading to a prom night filled with terror.

title: The Life List
description: After the death of her mother, Alex revisits her childhood aspirations, endeavoring to achieve her old goals, only to discover that pursuing these lifelong dreams takes her on an unforeseen and surprising journey.

title: Crazxy
description: In this edge-of-the-seat thriller, Dr. Abhimanyu Sood, a talented surgeon, races against time to rescue his daughter from a kidnapper. Charged with medical negligence, he must confront the mistakes of his past to save her life.

title: Raid 2
description: Set in 1989 Rajasthan, IRS officer Amay Patnaik (Ajay Devgn) returns to confront a new adversary, Dada Manohar Bhai (Riteish Deshmukh), a revered politician involved in a corrupt nexus. As Patnaik delves deeper into the layers of deceit, he faces challenges that test his resolve to uphold justice.
